The paper deals with a generalization of the Set Cover problem in the context of geometric set systems, which suggests that it belongs to the computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. The use of LP rounding schemes and approximation guarantees also indicates that it could belong to the data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), game theory (cs.GT), or information theory (cs.IT) sub-categories.
